comments.body:
I have been trying to do something "smart" as reading from the end of the file etc. but performance wise it was actually worse when number of commands to print is cca equal to number of lines in history file. What I measured, it was not significantly faster on default output either (processing last 1000 lines). Just reading whole file to a list and printing just a subset of that is just enough. My history file has 28 MB, containing 400k lines and it just prints it below 2 seconds.

file containing 1000 lines
{code:java}
real    0m0,706s
user    0m1,749s
sys     0m0,175s
{code}
file containing 400k lines
{code:java}
real    0m0,804s
user    0m1,914s
sys     0m0,196s
{code}
